Adds the cleanup_asa_unknown_relabel.py script + manifest CSV +
dry-run findings doc for the cef-asa-flip-and-relabel PR.

Phase 1 re-validation (against current data/13f.duckdb) confirms
investigation baseline (commit 79350a5) holds at execution time:
  - ASA UNKNOWN cohort: 350 rows / $1,752,484,930.87
  - Period coverage: 2024-11 (108), 2025-02 (112), 2025-08 (130)
  - SYN_0001230869 companion: 0 rows for the 3 target periods
  - Accessions: BACKFILL_MIG015_UNKNOWN_<period> (all 3 confirmed)

Phase 1.4 N-PORT byte-identical re-verification:
  - 2024-11: \$0.000000 delta (UNKNOWN \$439.91M = N-PORT \$439.91M)
  - 2025-02: \$0.000000 delta (UNKNOWN \$521.34M = N-PORT \$521.34M)
  - 2025-08: \$0.000000 delta (UNKNOWN \$791.24M = N-PORT \$791.24M)
  - Per-row: 350/350 byte_identical, 0 mismatch, 0 orphan

Manifest column entity_id_correction='11278->26793' records the
fund-attribution override on every relabeled row. UNKNOWN-side
entity_id=11278 (fund-typed entity literally named 'N/A' rolling
up to entity_id=63 = 'Calamos Investments') is replaced with
SYN_0001230869's canonical entity_id=26793 ('ASA Gold and Precious
Metals LTD Fund' self-rollup), mirroring the existing 2025-11 SYN
row. Holding-level columns copy verbatim from UNKNOWN.

Phase 3 entry gate satisfied (0 HOLD rows). --confirm next.

